item.title: Help please
item.dc:creator: @We_Dot_Pk We Dot Pk
item.description:
@We_Dot_Pk wrote:

On another topic

To navigate your way to the command prompt click “start” in your bottom, left-hand corner. Then a list will appear. To the right of the list you will see “run…”. Open that, and in the window that appears there will be a field. Type in that “cmd” and press enter. Once you have done this a black screen will appear. Simply type “ipconfig” and press enter. Viola, your ip details will be supplied.

And then what do i do with these ip things?
